des:
Enables Amazon Alexa support for CAME Connect. You can control your devices individually or group them with the help of the Alexa App. To use your device you need to have a valid CAME Connect account. You need to install one the CAME Connect cloud bridges one of the CAME automation in your home. After you succesfully configured the system you can install this Alexa Skill and start to control your blinds in your home

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1). Download our "CAME Connect Setup" app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Setup the CAME system with your Gateway and Automation;
(4). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(5). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "CAME Connect Smart Control";
(6). Click Enable skill of "CAME Connect Smart Control", then input your account username, password on the linking page;
(7). Let Alexa App discover automatically your devices or, alternatively, talk to Echo "Alexa,discover devices". Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(8). Now all setup is compled.

Try to say:
 - Alexa, open the balcony shutters
 - Alexa, close the kitchen shades
 - Alexa, what is the state of the irrigation valve?

It is recommended to use Alexa routines to define customized command sentences

For more information visit https://download.cameconnect.net/manual/alexa/CAMEConnectSmartControl.pdf

For technical support please contact: serviceinternational@came.com
